EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to substance use disorders; revising the
membership of the Statewide Substance Use Response
Working Group; revising the date by which the Working
Group must submit a certain report; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Statewide Substance Use Response Working Group in
2 the Office of the Attorney General to leverage and expand efforts by state and local
3 governmental entities to reduce the use of substances which are associated with
4 substance use disorders. Existing law further: (1) provides that the membership of
5 the Working Group consists of 18 members, 12 of whom are appointed by the
6 Attorney General; and (2) requires the Working Group to submit to the Governor,
7 the Attorney General and the Legislature on or before January 31 of each year a
8 report which includes recommendations for programs to address substance misuse
9 and substance use disorders. (NRS 458.460, 458.480) Section 1 of this bill provides
10 that, for purposes of membership of the Working Group, the designee of the
11 Director of the Department of Health and Human Services must be a person from
12 within the Division of Public and Behavioral Health of the Department. Section 1
13 also adds to the membership of the Working Group: (1) the Executive Director of
14 the Department of Indigent Defense Services, or his or her designee; and (2) four
15 members appointed by the Attorney General. Section 1.5 of this bill requires the
16 Working Group to submit the report on or before August 1 of each year, rather than
17 on or before January 31 of each year.
